<TITLE> DMC reopens Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka Medical College will reopen on Saturday, the principal said Wednesday. Dr Kazi Deen Mohammad told bdnews24.com after a meeting of the academic council that the residential halls would be opened to students on Friday and classes would start on Saturday. Authorities on March 31 closed the country's premier medical college for indefinite period after overnight clashes between two factions of the pro-Awami League student body that left one Bangladesh Chhatra League leader dead and no fewer than two dozens injured. The violence between two BCL factions at Fazle Rabbi Hall had left the general secretary of college's BCL unit, Abul Kalam Asad Rajib, critically injured. He died from his injuries in hospital later in the day. b
